quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  7,148,"And the people of Moses took during his absence a calf made of their ornaments, and ruddy like gold, and lowing. Saw they not that it could not speak to them, nor guide them in the way? Yet they took if for a God and became offenders"
  7,149,"But when they repented, and saw that they had erred, they said, Truly if our Lord have not mercy on us, and forgive us, we shall surely be of those who perish"
  7,150,"And when Moses returned to his people, wrathful, angered, he said, \"Evil is it that ye have done next upon my departure. Would ye hasten on the judgments of your Lord?\" And he threw down the tables, and seized his brother by the head and dragged him unto him. Said he, \"Son of my mother! the people thought me weak, and had well nigh slain me. Make not mine enemies to rejoice over me, and place me not among the wrong doers"
  7,151,"He said, \"O Lord, forgive me and my brother, and bring us into thy mercy; for of those who shew mercy thou art the most merciful"